                                         CAPE TOWN - An Animal Welfare Society  inspector has been shot and wounded during the hijacking of an official vehicle. The society says the specially fitted bakkie was hijacked close to its offices in Phillipi. The inspector has been transported to hospital. The society's CEO John McMullen said: “One of my inspectors was leaving with my secretary to go to the bank to deposit the weekend’s takings and they were attacked and hijacked.”